The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's decision to terminate the United States' participation in the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA), also known as the Iran Deal. The author argues that the deal was one-sided and a bad transaction for the United States. They believe that Iran negotiated the deal in bad faith and that it gave the Iranian regime too much in exchange for too little. President Trump aims to prevent Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon and address the threats posed by the regime's malign activities.